06:03.580 --> 06:05.408
-HEY.
-HEY.

06:06.975 --> 06:10.239
-HOW ARE YOU HOLDING UP?
-NEVER HAD A BETTER DAY.

06:11.501 --> 06:15.200
-I MEAN ABOUT TONIGHT,
GAYLE COMING TO TOWN.
YOU NERVOUS?

06:15.331 --> 06:17.507
-NO. NO.

06:17.638 --> 06:19.291
HOBIE IS REALLY LOOKING FORWARD
TO SEEING HER.

06:19.422 --> 06:21.424
-I DIDN'T ASK
ABOUT HOW HOBIE FELT.

06:23.165 --> 06:24.775
-I DON'T KNOW, STEPH.

06:24.906 --> 06:26.734
I DON'T KNOW HOW I FEEL ANYMORE.

06:27.996 --> 06:31.478
I MEAN, EVERY TIME GAYLE CALLS,
ALL WE DO IS TALK ABOUT HOBIE
AND PARENTAL THINGS.

06:31.608 --> 06:33.784
THE WHOLE THING
IS TOTALLY IMPERSONAL.

06:33.915 --> 06:36.787
THEN ALL OF A SUDDEN,
I REMEMBER SOMETHING
WE DID TOGETHER, AND I...

06:37.875 --> 06:40.138
I FEEL ALL THIS LOVE FOR HER.

06:40.269 --> 06:42.402
AND NOTHING TO DO WITH REALITY.

06:44.795 --> 06:45.709
-MAYBE IT DOES.

06:46.362 --> 06:48.625
I MEAN, WHO KNOWS?

06:48.756 --> 06:51.106
HOBIE STILL HAS HIS FANTASY
ABOUT HIS PARENTS GETTING
BACK TOGETHER SOMEDAY.

06:52.368 --> 06:54.239
KIDS DON'T LET THAT DREAM
DIE EASILY, YOU KNOW.

06:54.936 --> 06:56.372
-MAYBE I'M STILL A KID AT HEART.

07:00.855 --> 07:02.334
-I CAN BACK YOU UP TONIGHT
IF YOU WANT.

07:04.380 --> 07:07.035
-MY LIFE IS
COMPLICATED ENOUGH ALREADY.

07:07.949 --> 07:09.080
HAVE A NICE DAY, HUH?

07:12.301 --> 07:13.476
-DON'T SAY I DIDN'T OFFER.

07:25.488 --> 07:27.098
-YOUR MOTHER IS VERY UPSET.

07:28.186 --> 07:31.363
SHE FEELS YOU CARE
MORE ABOUT YOUR JOB
THAN YOU DO YOUR FAMILY.

07:31.973 --> 07:33.540
-WHY ARE YOU PUTTING ME
IN THIS POSITION, DAD?

07:34.366 --> 07:35.672
MAKING ME HAVE TO CHOOSE?

07:35.803 --> 07:37.108
-BECAUSE THERE'S NO WAY
AROUND IT, MATT.

07:37.848 --> 07:39.807
YOUR MOTHER AND I
ARE MOVING TO EUROPE.

07:39.937 --> 07:41.286
EITHER YOU CHOOSE
TO COME WITH US,
OR YOU DON'T.

07:41.417 --> 07:43.114
-AND IF I DON'T?

07:43.245 --> 07:45.465
-IF YOU CHOOSE
TO CUT YOURSELF OFF
FROM THE FAMILY,

07:45.595 --> 07:48.555
I'LL BE FORCED TO CUT YOU OFF
FROM EVERYTHING THIS FAMILY
PROVIDES YOU.

07:48.685 --> 07:50.078
AND I MEAN EVERYTHING.

07:50.208 --> 07:51.383
-FORCED BY WHO?

07:52.167 --> 07:53.211
WHO IS FORCING YOU?

07:53.342 --> 07:54.822
-YOU ARE.

07:54.952 --> 07:57.302
BY BEING SELFISH,
THINKING ONLY OF YOURSELF.

07:57.433 --> 07:59.479
-OH, ME?

07:59.609 --> 08:01.611
YOU'RE THE ONE THAT'S
MAKING ALL THE DECISIONS
AND NOT TELLING US.

08:01.742 --> 08:04.309
-WHEN YOU BECOME A PARENT,
YOU'LL BE ABLE TO MAKE
THE DECISIONS.

08:04.440 --> 08:06.442
UNTIL THEN,
I'M THE HEAD OF THIS FAMILY.

08:07.095 --> 08:08.705
-WHAT ABOUT LOVE
AND UNDERSTANDING?

08:09.793 --> 08:11.229
ISN'T THAT PART OF PARENTING?

08:12.230 --> 08:13.971
-IF WE DIDN'T LOVE YOU,

08:14.102 --> 08:15.930
WE WOULDN'T CARE
WHETHER YOU CAME WITH US
OR NOT, WOULD WE?

08:23.415 --> 08:24.678
-BEAUTIFUL DAY, ISN'T IT?

08:24.808 --> 08:26.680
-YEAH.
-BYE.

08:42.870 --> 08:44.654
-[TELEPHONE RINGING]

08:45.655 --> 08:47.135
-BUCHANNON.

08:47.265 --> 08:48.440
-GAYLE: HELLO, MITCH.

08:48.571 --> 08:50.878
-GAYLE. GAYLE, HI.

08:51.008 --> 08:52.575
HEY, I CAN HARDLY HEAR YOU.

08:52.706 --> 08:54.838
-I'M STILL IN THE AIR.
WE SHOULD BE LANDING SOON.

08:54.969 --> 08:57.058
-GREAT, GREAT.
HOBIE AND I WILL MEET YOU
AT THE AIRPORT.

08:57.188 --> 08:59.582
-NO, NO, MITCH, THAT'S OKAY.

08:59.713 --> 09:01.323
I'VE MADE ARRANGEMENTS.

09:02.237 --> 09:05.196
HOW ABOUT
I'LL JUST MEET YOU GUYS
AT YOUR PLACE AROUND 5:00?

09:05.327 --> 09:06.937
-YEAH, YEAH, THAT'S PERFECT.

09:07.068 --> 09:09.853
GAYLE, HOBIE CAN'T WAIT
TO SEE YOU.

09:09.984 --> 09:12.029
-OH, I CAN'T WAIT TO SEE HIM.

09:12.160 --> 09:14.510
-TELL ME ABOUT
THIS SURPRISE OF YOURS.

09:14.641 --> 09:16.207
-I'LL TELL YOU
WHEN I SEE YOU AND HOBIE.

09:16.338 --> 09:18.079
-NO, NO, NO, TELL ME NOW.

09:18.209 --> 09:19.428
-BYE, MITCH.

09:22.562 --> 09:24.302
-I HATE SURPRISES.

09:33.703 --> 09:34.704
-HOW ARE YOU DOING?

09:35.705 --> 09:38.055
-WELL, I'M EXCITED,

09:38.186 --> 09:39.796
AND I'M NERVOUS,

09:40.841 --> 09:42.059
AND I'M IN LOVE.

09:42.190 --> 09:43.234
-[CLICKS TONGUE] OH!

09:57.509 --> 09:59.424
-HEY, DAD!

09:59.555 --> 10:01.122
DAD! DAD!

10:01.252 --> 10:03.646
-JARRED, CAREFUL.
-SORRY.

10:03.777 --> 10:05.735
-WHAT IS IT?

10:05.866 --> 10:06.997
-WELL, YOU SAID
YOU'D WORK FOR AN HOUR
AND THEN WATCH ME BOOGIE BOARD.

10:07.128 --> 10:09.086
-AND I WILL.
I WILL. I PROMISE.

10:09.217 --> 10:10.871
-THAT WAS TWO HOURS AGO.

10:12.002 --> 10:14.135
COME ON. COME ON.
WATCH ME, PLEASE!

10:14.265 --> 10:15.789
-OKAY. ALL RIGHT. ALL RIGHT.

10:16.572 --> 10:18.705
-[MOBILE PHONE RINGING]
-HOLD ON JUST A SEC.

10:19.967 --> 10:22.186
-YEAH, WADE PETERSON.
-MAN: WADE, IT'S SAM.

10:22.317 --> 10:24.145
-SAM! SAM, I'VE BEEN TRYING
TO REACH YOU ALL DAY.

10:24.275 --> 10:26.277
WHAT THE HELL IS GOING ON
IN FLORIDA?

10:26.408 --> 10:28.453
-THEY CANCELED THE ORDER.
THEY WANNA SEND
THE T-41 INSTEAD.

10:28.584 --> 10:30.891
-WHAT AM I SUPPOSED
TO DO WITH THAT?
-YOU COULD STALL A WEEK OR TWO.

10:31.021 --> 10:33.328
-WELL, GINO TELLS ME
I CAN'T GET A SHIPMENT
FOR THREE WEEKS.

10:33.458 --> 10:36.418
I NEED EVERYTHING IN
MY OFFICE BY FRIDAY AFTERNOON,
OR THE DEAL FALLS APART.

10:36.548 --> 10:37.593
NOW, COME ON.

10:41.771 --> 10:43.599
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

11:12.628 --> 11:14.674
-POSSIBLE SUBMERSION, TOWER 10.

11:29.689 --> 11:33.649
-MAN: [ON RADIO]
2-11, RESPOND CODE THREE TO
POSSIBLE SUBMERSION. TOWER 10.

11:36.217 --> 11:38.654
-MATT, HURRY.
WE'VE GOT A SUBMERSION
ON TOWER 10.

11:42.397 --> 11:44.965
-EVERYBODY GET OUT OF THE WATER!

12:25.832 --> 12:28.095
-MAN: [ON RADIO]
BAYWATCH SCARAB 1 TO 295.

12:28.225 --> 12:30.750
WE COPY YOUR TRANSMISSION
AND ARE RESPONDING CODE THREE
TO TOWER 10. OVER.

12:30.880 --> 12:32.795
-[SIREN BLARING]

12:35.842 --> 12:38.192
-MAN: [ON RADIO]
207 LINCOLN TO 214.

12:38.322 --> 12:42.762
LIFEGUARDS IN THE WATER.
STRAIGHT-LINE SEARCH PATTERN.
VICTIM UNKNOWN AND UNIDENTIFIED.

12:42.892 --> 12:44.720
SUBMERSION
REMAINS A POSSIBILITY.

13:38.165 --> 13:40.776
-HOW LONG HAS HE BEEN DOWN?
-ABOUT FIVE MINUTES.

14:27.388 --> 14:29.694
-MAN: [ON RADIO]
BAYWATCH SCARABS INDICATE
A LATERAL DRIFT.

14:29.825 --> 14:32.654
MOVE THE STRAIGHT-LINE SEARCH
SOUTH 50 METERS.

14:32.784 --> 14:35.091
REPEAT, SOUTH 50 METERS.

14:35.222 --> 14:37.398
SUBMERSION BACKUP PROCEDURES
IN PLACE.

14:37.528 --> 14:39.661
PARAMEDICS
AND HOSPITAL NOTIFIED.

14:39.791 --> 14:42.011
MEDEVAC HELICOPTERS STANDING BY.

14:46.407 --> 14:48.496
-295, THIS IS MATT BRODY
NEEDING BACKUP.

14:48.626 --> 14:50.280
-WHAT'S GOING ON OUT THERE?
-NOT NOW, SIR.
THERE'S A KID IN TROUBLE.

14:50.411 --> 14:52.500
-MATT, GET A DIVING TEAM HERE
RIGHT NOW.

14:52.630 --> 14:54.676
-WAIT. THAT'S HIS BOARD.

14:54.806 --> 14:56.939
WHERE IS HE?
-WHAT DID YOUR SON LOOK LIKE?
WHAT WAS HE WEARING?

14:57.070 --> 15:00.725
-UH, HE'S 10. BLOND.
HE'S GOT BLACK SHORTS ON
WITH PURPLE, PINK...

15:00.856 --> 15:03.554
-HEY, I SAW A KID
THAT LOOKED JUST LIKE THAT
BEHIND THE JETTY.

15:03.685 --> 15:05.034
OVER THERE.

15:20.658 --> 15:22.486
-NOW, YOU LISTEN TO ME.

15:22.617 --> 15:24.358
WHAT IF SOMEONE
WAS REALLY DROWNING OUT THERE

15:24.488 --> 15:26.360
WHILE ALL OF MY LIFEGUARDS
WERE LOOKING FOR YOU?

15:26.490 --> 15:28.928
YOU PUT PEOPLE'S LIVES
IN DANGER, SON.

15:29.885 --> 15:31.582
-I'M SORRY.

15:31.713 --> 15:34.150
-HOW COULD YOU HAVE PULLED
SUCH A STUPID STUNT, JARRED?

15:34.281 --> 15:36.152
WHAT WERE YOU THINKING?

15:36.283 --> 15:37.893
ANSWER ME.

15:38.024 --> 15:41.027
-WELL, YOU SAID WE WERE GONNA
SPEND THE DAY TOGETHER,

15:41.157 --> 15:43.638
BUT YOU ACTED
LIKE I WASN'T EVEN THERE.

15:44.465 --> 15:48.817
I FIGURED MAYBE YOU'D NOTICE
IF YOU THOUGHT I WAS DEAD.

16:01.525 --> 16:02.657
-MR. PETERSON?

16:04.398 --> 16:06.617
I KNOW YOUR WORK IS IMPORTANT,

16:06.748 --> 16:08.315
BUT SO IS
THE TIME WITH YOUR SON.

16:10.491 --> 16:13.059
HE NEEDS TO KNOW
HE'S AS IMPORTANT TO YOU
AS ANYTHING ELSE.

16:13.929 --> 16:16.497
-I THOUGHT YOUR LIFEGUARD DUTIES
ENDED WITH RESCUE.

16:16.627 --> 16:19.630
-WELL, JARRED REMINDS ME
OF MYSELF WHEN I WAS HIS AGE.

16:20.544 --> 16:23.678
I JUST DON'T WANT HIM
TO GROW UP TO FEEL
THE WAY I DO ABOUT MY FATHER.

16:25.419 --> 16:27.421
-YEAH. THANK YOU.

16:41.565 --> 16:44.655
-AH, THERE YOU ARE.
-HEY.

16:46.396 --> 16:48.616
MOM, WHAT HAPPENED?
I THOUGHT YOU WERE JOB-HUNTING.

16:48.746 --> 16:49.747
-I WAS.

16:49.878 --> 16:51.445
I HUNTED THEM DOWN.

16:51.575 --> 16:53.099
I HAD THEM IN MY SIGHTS.

16:53.229 --> 16:55.840
I TOOK AIM, AND PFFT!

16:55.971 --> 16:58.234
THEY ALL GOT AWAY,
EVERY SINGLE ONE.

16:59.235 --> 17:01.194
OH, WHAT A DAY!

17:01.324 --> 17:02.934
LISTEN, HONEY,
I'M GONNA GO TO THE BEACH HUT
AND GRAB A BURGER.

17:03.065 --> 17:04.414
CAN I GET YOU ANYTHING?

17:04.545 --> 17:06.025
-MOM, THE BEACH HUT
LOST THEIR LEASE.

17:06.155 --> 17:08.243
THEY HAD TO CLOSE DOWN.

17:08.375 --> 17:11.682
-NO! THAT WAS
THE ONLY DECENT PLACE
TO GET ANY FOOD AROUND HERE.

17:11.813 --> 17:14.642
-YEAH, I KNOW.
TELL ME ABOUT IT.
-[GRUMBLES]

17:15.946 --> 17:18.211
UH, LISTEN, SUMMER,
DO YOU HAVE A MINUTE TO TALK?

17:18.950 --> 17:20.865
-NO, NOT REALLY. WHY?

17:21.953 --> 17:23.607
-I'VE BEEN THINKING
ABOUT A FEW THINGS.

17:23.738 --> 17:25.869
-SOMETHING REALLY TERRIBLE
ALWAYS HAPPENS

17:26.001 --> 17:28.047
WHEN YOU SAY YOU'VE BEEN
THINKING ABOUT A FEW THINGS.

17:28.176 --> 17:30.440
-WELL, I'VE BEEN THINKING, UH...

17:32.007 --> 17:33.704
WE SHOULD MOVE
BACK TO PITTSBURGH.

17:33.835 --> 17:35.402
-I KNEW IT.

17:35.532 --> 17:39.623
-HONEY, I CAN'T FIND
A GOOD JOB HERE. I'VE TRIED.

17:40.711 --> 17:43.366
UNCLE LEO OFFERED ME
A REALLY GOOD ONE BACK HOME.

17:43.497 --> 17:45.281
-YEAH, WELL, MOM, WHAT ABOUT ME?

17:45.412 --> 17:48.110
I MEAN, HOW AM I SUPPOSED TO DO
MY JOB BACK IN PITTSBURGH?

19:22.073 --> 19:23.249
-[SIGHS]

19:23.379 --> 19:25.120
THIS IS MY FAVORITE TIME OF DAY,

19:25.251 --> 19:27.862
WHEN EVERYONE HAS GONE HOME,
AND THE BEACH IS OURS.

19:30.473 --> 19:32.301
-UNLESS YOU DON'T HAVE
A HOME TO GO HOME TO.

19:33.259 --> 19:35.217
-WHAT HAPPENED?
DID YOU TALK TO YOUR FATHER?

19:38.133 --> 19:41.310
-HE SAID IF I DON'T MOVE
BACK TO FRANCE WITH THEM,
HE'S GONNA CUT ME OFF.

19:43.791 --> 19:45.314
AND LEAVE ME HERE WITH NOTHING.

19:46.228 --> 19:47.969
-IT'S A TOUCH DECISION, MATT.

19:50.232 --> 19:52.930
BUT YOU'RE 18-YEARS-OLD,
AND IT'S YOUR DECISION.

19:55.803 --> 19:56.978
COME WORK OUT WITH ME.

19:57.108 --> 19:58.458
YOU'LL FEEL BETTER.

19:59.546 --> 20:02.592
-NO. I WANNA FINISH THIS.

20:02.723 --> 20:03.898
-WHAT IS IT?

20:04.028 --> 20:05.813
-A POEM, LYRICS.

20:05.943 --> 20:07.771
I DON'T KNOW.

20:07.902 --> 20:08.859
-CAN I READ IT?

20:10.252 --> 20:11.645
-IT'S NOT FINISHED.

20:11.775 --> 20:13.168
-I DON'T CARE.

20:18.869 --> 20:22.699
THE DAY WAS MOVING WESTWARD
LEAVING COLORS IN THE SKY

20:22.830 --> 20:27.051
THE EASTERN BLACK WAS CHASING
MOVING COLORS THAT HAD DIED

20:27.182 --> 20:30.185
THE DAY WAS RACING QUICKLY
BUT COULD NOT OUTRUN THE NIGHT

20:30.316 --> 20:33.928
AND I RODE ALONG THE SEASHORE
TO THE CAVERNS OF DELIGHT

20:37.366 --> 20:38.802
MATT, THIS IS BEAUTIFUL.

20:41.588 --> 20:43.242
-EXCEPT THERE AREN'T
ANY CAVERNS OF DELIGHT.

20:44.765 --> 20:46.941
LISTEN, DO YOU MIND IF I SLEEP
AT HEADQUARTERS TONIGHT?

20:47.855 --> 20:49.030
