24:20.807 --> 24:22.461
HI.
-HI.

24:23.766 --> 24:24.680
YOU LOOK BEAUTIFUL.

24:24.811 --> 24:26.639
-OH, THANKS.

24:26.769 --> 24:29.076
UH...
WELL, THE PLACE LOOKS GREAT.

24:29.206 --> 24:31.034
WHAT DID YOU GUYS DO,
REDECORATE?

24:31.165 --> 24:33.733
-KIND OF. WE CLEANED.

24:35.561 --> 24:37.301
-UH, CAN I GET YOU
A DRINK OR SOMETHING?

24:37.432 --> 24:39.129
-NO. NO, THANKS.

24:42.306 --> 24:43.917
SO HOW WAS
THAT GEOGRAPHY REPORT?

24:44.047 --> 24:45.396
DID YOU GET THOSE MAPS
I SENT YOU?

24:45.527 --> 24:46.920
-YEAH, THEY WERE RIGHT-ON.
I GOT AN A.

24:47.050 --> 24:48.965
-AW, THAT'S MY BOY.

24:50.184 --> 24:51.011
GOD, YOU LOOK GOOD.

24:51.141 --> 24:52.882
-MITCH, KEN JORDAN.

24:53.013 --> 24:54.405
GAYLE HAS TOLD ME
A LOT ABOUT YOU.

24:55.189 --> 24:56.059
-KEN, I...

24:56.973 --> 24:58.975
-I KNOW. I COULDN'T WAIT
IN THE CAR ANY LONGER.

25:00.629 --> 25:04.677
JUST A FEW MINUTES AWAY
FROM THIS PRECIOUS WOMAN
SEEMS LIKE AN ETERNITY.

25:07.636 --> 25:08.985
AND YOU MUST BE HOBIE.

25:10.813 --> 25:12.554
I'VE HEARD MORE THAN A LOT
ABOUT YOU.

25:12.685 --> 25:14.034
-HEY. NICE TO MEET YOU.

25:14.861 --> 25:16.558
-SO DID YOU, UH,
TELL THEM OUR NEWS?

25:17.385 --> 25:19.430
-NO, SHE HASN'T.

25:21.389 --> 25:22.346
-WHAT NEWS?

25:22.477 --> 25:24.348
-UH... [LAUGHS NERVOUSLY]

25:24.479 --> 25:27.395
WELL, YOU REMEMBER I TOLD YOU
THAT I HAD A SURPRISE?

25:28.439 --> 25:29.615
WELL, UM...

25:30.224 --> 25:31.486
KEN AND I ARE GETTING MARRIED.

25:36.535 --> 25:37.927
-THIS WEEKEND.

25:52.289 --> 25:53.943
-I SHOULD HAVE TOLD YOU, I KNOW,

25:54.074 --> 25:59.209
BUT THERE WAS JUST NEVER
A GOOD TIME TO SPILL THE BEANS.

25:59.340 --> 26:02.778
I MEAN, TELLING YOU
ON THE TELEPHONE
SEEMED SO IMPERSONAL.

26:02.909 --> 26:05.172
AND BESIDES,
I WANTED HOBIE TO MEET HIM.

26:05.302 --> 26:07.348
AFTER ALL,
KEN IS GOING TO BE HIS...

26:07.478 --> 26:09.393
-HOBIE'S STEP-FATHER.

26:09.524 --> 26:11.308
I GET THE PICTURE.

26:12.309 --> 26:15.486
-I'D REALLY LIKE HOBIE
TO COME WITH US TO ACAPULCO
FOR THE WEDDING THIS WEEKEND.

26:15.617 --> 26:17.140
-WELL, HE'S GOT A PARTY
HE WANTS TO GO TO.

26:17.271 --> 26:18.620
-YEAH, YEAH,
HE TOLD ME ABOUT IT,

26:18.751 --> 26:20.666
BUT HE SAID
HE'D RATHER COME WITH US.

26:21.492 --> 26:22.885
-OH.

26:23.016 --> 26:25.409
-MITCH...
-NO, NO, NO. IT'S NO PROBLEM.

26:25.540 --> 26:27.803
I'LL DRIVE HIM TO THE AIRPORT.
WHICH AIRLINE?

26:27.934 --> 26:31.285
-UH, ACTUALLY, WE'RE FLYING
ON KEN'S CORPORATE JET.

26:31.415 --> 26:33.026
-[CHUCKLING] OH.

26:33.156 --> 26:34.680
HE HAS HIS OWN JET, HUH?

26:34.810 --> 26:36.464
WELL, THAT'S A NICE CATCH.

26:36.595 --> 26:39.032
-KEN WORKED VERY HARD
TO GET WHERE HE IS.

26:39.162 --> 26:41.251
AND HE HAPPENS TO BE
VERY DOWN-TO-EARTH,
AND YOU WOULD LIKE HIM.

26:41.382 --> 26:43.558
-I'M SORRY. I'M...

26:43.689 --> 26:46.039
I'M SURE HE'S A GREAT GUY.

26:46.169 --> 26:47.475
GAYLE, I REALLY WANT YOU
TO BE HAPPY.

26:47.606 --> 26:49.346
-I WANT US ALL TO BE HAPPY.

26:50.304 --> 26:51.131
ESPECIALLY HOBIE.

26:51.261 --> 26:52.567
-HOBIE IS HAPPY.

26:52.698 --> 26:54.656
-I MEAN REALLY HAPPY.

26:55.265 --> 26:58.225
LOOK, KEN COULD BE
THE MOST WONDERFUL INFLUENCE
ON HOBIE.

26:58.355 --> 26:59.574
HE COULD PROVIDE HIM
WITH SO MUCH.

26:59.705 --> 27:00.967
-YOU MEAN BUY HIM SO MUCH?

27:01.097 --> 27:03.230
-NO, THAT IS NOT
WHAT I MEANT AT ALL,

27:03.360 --> 27:05.232
AND AS USUAL,
YOU'RE TWISTING MY WORDS.

27:07.843 --> 27:09.802
-YOU WANT HOBIE
TO COME LIVE WITH YOU,
DON'T YOU?

27:11.151 --> 27:12.631
ISN'T THAT WHAT
THIS WHOLE THING IS ABOUT?

27:15.242 --> 27:17.244
-YES.
-FORGET IT.

27:17.374 --> 27:19.594
-MITCH...
-I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE DOING THIS.

27:19.725 --> 27:21.857
-LOOK, I DON'T WANNA DO IT,
BUT...

27:22.858 --> 27:26.732
BUT I HAVE SEEN AN ATTORNEY,
AND I WILL GO TO COURT
IF I HAVE TO.

27:38.395 --> 27:40.441
-IS THIS YOUR CARD?

27:41.921 --> 27:43.009
-HOW DID YOU DO THAT?

27:43.139 --> 27:44.271
-MAGIC.

27:47.578 --> 27:49.668
-DAD, KEN DOES
THE COOLEST CARD TRICK.

27:49.798 --> 27:50.625
COME CHECK THIS OUT.

27:50.756 --> 27:52.192
KEN, DO ONE FOR MY DAD.

27:52.322 --> 27:54.498
-ALL RIGHT, JUST ONE.
GO AHEAD. PICK ANY CARD.

27:55.761 --> 27:56.892
PUT IT BACK ANYWHERE YOU WANT.

27:59.068 --> 28:00.374
BEAUTIFUL.

28:00.504 --> 28:01.636
LET'S SEE THIS HERE.

28:03.420 --> 28:05.814
OH, THAT'S YOUR CARD?

28:05.945 --> 28:07.468
-THAT'S IT.

28:07.598 --> 28:09.557
-ISN'T THAT THE COOLEST TRICK?

28:09.688 --> 28:11.167
-OH, THAT'S TERRIFIC. YEAH.

28:12.081 --> 28:15.519
-UH, I HATE TO INTERRUPT
THIS MAGICAL MOMENT HERE,

28:15.650 --> 28:18.522
BUT WE'VE GOT
AN EARLY DAY TOMORROW.
-YEAH.

28:19.436 --> 28:20.960
-DAD, KEN HAS HIS OWN JET.

28:21.090 --> 28:23.527
-YEAH. YEAH, I HEARD.
THAT'S REALLY GREAT.

28:23.658 --> 28:25.355
-WELL, I'M GLAD
I FINALLY GOT TO MEET YOU.

28:25.486 --> 28:27.749
LOOKS LIKE WE'RE GONNA HAVE
A LOT OF THINGS IN COMMON.

28:27.880 --> 28:29.795
-YEAH, LOOKS LIKE IT.

28:31.884 --> 28:35.539
-HOBSTER, I WANNA PUT YOU
IN THE COCKPIT OF THAT PLANE
TOMORROW,

28:35.670 --> 28:38.020
AND YOU'RE GONNA FLY
FOR A COUPLE OF MILES.

28:38.151 --> 28:38.978
-ALL RIGHT!

28:42.068 --> 28:43.460
WHOA!
-OH, MISSED YOU.

28:46.333 --> 28:47.856
-I'LL SEE YOU
IN THE MORNING, SWEETIE.
-ALL RIGHT.

28:47.987 --> 28:49.553
BYE BYE.
-BYE.

28:53.383 --> 28:54.733
-I'M GONNA GO PACK.

28:54.863 --> 28:55.821
-WAIT A MINUTE.

28:57.736 --> 28:59.825
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
TEACHING HIM OUR HANDSHAKE?

28:59.955 --> 29:01.565
-WELL, HE TAUGHT ME ONE
HE USED TO DO IN COLLEGE.

29:01.696 --> 29:02.653
IT'S REALLY COOL.
YOU WANNA SEE IT?

29:02.784 --> 29:03.872
-NO, I DON'T.

29:05.526 --> 29:06.875
-DAD?
-WHAT?

29:08.529 --> 29:09.965
-I WON'T GO
IF YOU DON'T WANT ME TO.

29:17.059 --> 29:20.019
-NO, I WANT YOU TO GO.
GOD, I WANT YOU TO GO.

29:20.149 --> 29:21.803
DO ME A BIG FAVOR, HUH?
-OKAY.

29:21.934 --> 29:23.283
-FLY THAT JET, HUH?
-ALL RIGHT.

29:23.413 --> 29:24.806
-OKAY.
-I LOVE YOU, DAD.

29:24.937 --> 29:26.721
-ALL RIGHT. LOVE YOU TOO.

29:26.852 --> 29:28.549
-SEE YOU IN THE MORNING.
-OKAY.

29:48.699 --> 29:50.223
-SUMMER: MOM, WAIT UP!

29:51.050 --> 29:52.834
MOM, WOULD YOU SLOW DOWN?

30:00.363 --> 30:02.626
MOM, WHAT IS WITH YOU TODAY?

30:02.757 --> 30:06.587
-OH, SUMMER,
I LOVE THIS RESTAURANT!

30:07.240 --> 30:10.678
-MOM, LISTEN,
THE BEACH HUT IS CLOSED.

30:10.809 --> 30:13.420
-OH, NO, IT'S NOT.
-YES, IT IS.

30:13.550 --> 30:17.337
-NO, IT'S NOT,
AND IT IS NOT
THE BEACH HUT ANYMORE.

30:17.467 --> 30:20.644
IT IS OUR BEACH HUT.
[EXCLAIMS]

30:21.471 --> 30:23.256
-OUR BEACH HUT?
MOM, WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

30:23.386 --> 30:24.910
-WELL, I LEASED IT. IT'S OURS.

30:25.040 --> 30:26.433
-YOU LEASED THIS?

30:27.782 --> 30:29.523
WELL, HOW? WITH WHAT MONEY?

30:29.653 --> 30:32.221
-WELL, I HAD ENOUGH
TO PUT DOWN A FIRST AND LAST.

30:32.352 --> 30:34.223
I MEAN, IT WAS EVERYTHING
THAT I HAVE, BUT...

30:34.963 --> 30:37.313
HONEY, I THINK
ONCE WE FIX THIS PLACE UP,

30:37.444 --> 30:39.185
THE MONEY IS JUST GONNA
ROLL IN LIKE WAVES.

30:39.315 --> 30:42.579
-OH, OKAY, AND WHERE DO WE GET
THIS MONEY TO FIX IT UP?

30:42.710 --> 30:44.886
-WOULD YOU STOP WORRYING?

30:45.495 --> 30:47.367
UH, WE'LL DO IT.

30:48.150 --> 30:49.717
OF COURSE, WE COULD
MOVE BACK TO PITTSBURGH.

30:52.154 --> 30:53.112
-SO WHAT DO YOU WANNA NAME IT?

30:53.242 --> 30:55.070
-OKAY, I WAS THINKING...

30:56.419 --> 30:57.856
JACKIE'S AT THE BEACH.

30:58.900 --> 31:00.032
-NO.
-NO?

31:00.162 --> 31:03.296
-HOW ABOUT A SUMMER PLACE?

31:04.079 --> 31:05.254
-REALLY BAD.

31:06.429 --> 31:08.127
OKAY, HOW ABOUT THIS?

31:08.257 --> 31:10.259
JACKIE'S SUMMER PLACE?

31:11.782 --> 31:13.959
-OKAY, I LIKE THAT.

31:16.004 --> 31:19.268
-OF COURSE, THE ONLY THING IS
IT'LL PROBABLY MAKE
YOUR JOB UNNECESSARY.

31:19.399 --> 31:22.968
YEAH, I MEAN,
'CAUSE EVERYONE WILL BE HERE
EATING MY FABULOUS FOOD,

31:23.098 --> 31:25.796
AND THERE WON'T BE ANYBODY
ON THE BEACH FOR YOU TO RESCUE.

31:25.927 --> 31:28.974
-LET'S JUST HOPE THE LIFEGUARDS
AREN'T HERE PUMPING
PEOPLE'S STOMACHS, OKAY?

31:29.104 --> 31:30.671
-OH, PUMPING THEIR STOMACHS?
-YES.

31:30.801 --> 31:32.281
-THAT'S JUST REALLY FUNNY.

31:32.412 --> 31:34.327
THAT'S JUST REALLY FUNNY.

31:35.415 --> 31:37.025
IT'S GONNA BE GREAT.
I LOVE IT!

31:43.336 --> 31:44.467
-HEY, DAD.
-HEY, PAL.

31:44.598 --> 31:46.208
MY GOD.

31:46.339 --> 31:48.036
YOU'RE GOING FOR THE WEEKEND,
NOT FOREVER.

31:50.647 --> 31:52.780
-WELL, YOU ALWAYS TELL ME
TO BE PREPARED FOR ANYTHING.

31:52.911 --> 31:54.738
-YEAH, I DID.

31:56.436 --> 31:57.611
YOU KNOW, PAL, UM...

31:58.612 --> 32:01.441
I HAVEN'T REALLY TALKED
ABOUT HOW YOU FEEL ABOUT
YOUR MOM MARRYING KEN.

32:02.268 --> 32:04.226
-WELL, YOU DIDN'T TELL ME
HOW YOU FEEL EITHER.

32:04.357 --> 32:05.880
-I ASKED YOU FIRST.

32:06.837 --> 32:07.708
-OKAY.

32:08.535 --> 32:11.799
WELL, HE'S A GREAT GUY
AND EVERYTHING.

32:11.930 --> 32:15.672
SO IF SHE'S GONNA MARRY ANYONE,
IT MIGHT AS WELL BE HIM.

32:18.240 --> 32:19.154
I ASKED YOU SECOND.

32:20.112 --> 32:21.330
-WELL, I, UH...

32:23.202 --> 32:25.378
I ALWAYS KNEW
THIS DAY WOULD COME.

32:27.380 --> 32:29.121
BUT IT'S HARD, YOU KNOW.

32:30.339 --> 32:31.340
I FEEL KIND OF SAD.

32:32.428 --> 32:33.864
I'LL GET OVER IT.

32:35.518 --> 32:36.389
-DAD.

32:37.999 --> 32:39.435
YOU KNOW I LOVE YOU.

32:40.654 --> 32:41.524
-YEAH.

32:42.308 --> 32:43.962
I LOVE YOU TOO.

32:44.092 --> 32:45.572
-[DOORBELL RINGS]

32:45.702 --> 32:47.661
-THAT'S MOM.
-YEAH.

32:47.791 --> 32:49.532
COME HERE.

32:54.363 --> 32:56.322
GET OUT OF HERE.
YOU HAVE A GOOD TIME
DOWN THERE, HUH?

32:56.452 --> 32:57.366
-ALL RIGHT.
-OKAY.

32:58.672 --> 33:01.501
ALL RIGHT, I'LL BRING YOU
BACK SOMETHING FROM MEXICO.

33:38.407 --> 33:42.020
-ELAINE, COME OVER HERE
AND SAY HI TO GAYLE'S SON,
HOBIE.

33:42.150 --> 33:43.499
-HELLO, HOBIE.
-HI. NICE TO MEET YOU.

33:43.630 --> 33:44.500
-YOU TOO.

33:44.631 --> 33:45.675
-ELAINE IS OUR PILOT.

33:45.806 --> 33:47.025
-YOU'RE A PILOT?

33:47.155 --> 33:48.939
-YEAH,
14 YEARS IN THE AIR FORCE.

33:49.070 --> 33:50.724
-WHAT DID YOU FLY?

33:50.854 --> 33:54.249
-LET'S SEE, UM, C-130S, F-16S,
JUST ABOUT EVERYTHING.

33:54.380 --> 33:57.470
-I'VE NEVER SEEN
A PLANE LIKE THIS ONE BEFORE.
IT'S LIKE A ROOM IN A HOUSE.

33:58.949 --> 34:00.951
-YOU WANNA SEE THE COCKPIT?
-DEFINITELY!

34:01.865 --> 34:03.389
-WELL, COME ON. LET'S GO.
-GREAT!

34:05.956 --> 34:08.002
-YOU HAPPY?
-MM-HMM.

34:08.132 --> 34:10.570
-LOOK, I KNOW
THIS HAS BEEN HARD FOR YOU,

34:10.699 --> 34:12.659
BUT HOBIE NEEDS
HIS MOTHER RIGHT NOW.

34:13.746 --> 34:15.053
-I HOPE SO.

34:15.183 --> 34:17.185
-SO GIVE ME A LITTLE SMILE.

34:17.315 --> 34:18.143
[SNORTS]

34:30.024 --> 34:32.025
-[GRUNTING]

34:40.947 --> 34:42.949
-WHOA! WHOA! TAKE IT EASY.

34:43.081 --> 34:45.779
SAVE SOME OF THAT BAG
FOR THE REST OF US.

34:52.742 --> 34:54.570
LOOKS LIKE IT DIDN'T GO SO WELL
WITH GAYLE, HUH?

34:54.701 --> 34:57.138
-OH. OH, I WOULDN'T SAY THAT.

34:58.183 --> 35:00.098
[ANGRILY]
GAYLE IS MARRYING A MILLIONAIRE

35:01.011 --> 35:03.188
WHO'S FLYING HER TO MEXICO

35:03.318 --> 35:05.451
ON HIS PRIVATE JET.

35:06.974 --> 35:09.324
SHE'S SUING ME FOR CUSTODY.

35:10.412 --> 35:14.721
AND HOBIE TAUGHT KEN
OUR SECRET HANDSHAKE.

35:16.549 --> 35:17.941
DIDN'T GO SO WELL?

35:18.072 --> 35:20.640
I'D SAY THE WHOLE THING
IS A COMPLETE DISASTER.

35:21.293 --> 35:23.599
-I'LL HOLD THE BAG FOR YOU.
-THANK YOU.

35:26.733 --> 35:28.474
KEN, HUH?

35:29.779 --> 35:32.173
OUR SECRET HANDSHAKE!

35:42.314 --> 35:43.837
-HEY.
-HEY.

35:45.099 --> 35:48.233
-WOW. YOU LOOK LIKE
YOU NEED ENERGY MORE THAN I DO.
HERE.

35:51.105 --> 35:53.107
WHAT DID YOU DO LAST NIGHT?

35:53.238 --> 35:54.369
-I SLEPT AT C.J. AND...

35:54.500 --> 35:56.110
-YOU AND C.J. SLEPT TOGETHER?

35:56.241 --> 35:57.938
-AT C.J. AND STEPHANIE'S.

35:58.982 --> 36:00.462
I SLEPT ON THE COUCH.

36:00.593 --> 36:03.117
OR TRIED TO.

36:03.248 --> 36:06.207
-WELL, WHY COULDN'T YOU SLEEP?
WHAT? WAS C.J. RUNNING AROUND
IN SOME SKIMPY, LITTLE NIGHTIE?

36:06.338 --> 36:09.341
-NO. I COULDN'T...
COULDN'T STOP THINKING.

36:09.471 --> 36:10.907
-WHY?

36:11.038 --> 36:13.823
-WELL, SHOULD I GO TO FRANCE
OR STAY HERE?

36:15.651 --> 36:19.002
YOU KNOW, THE CRAZY THING IS
THAT MY DAD HAS NEVER CARED
IF I WAS AROUND OR NOT.

36:19.133 --> 36:21.962
AND ALL OF A SUDDEN,
HE'S FORCING ME
TO GO BACK WITH HIM.

36:22.092 --> 36:25.139
-MATT, YOUR DAD
IS A CONTROL FREAK.
YOU KNOW THAT.

36:25.270 --> 36:28.795
SO DO NOT LET HIM FORCE YOU
INTO DOING ANYTHING
YOU DON'T WANNA DO.

36:29.752 --> 36:31.580
BESIDES, YOU ARE MY BEST FRIEND,

36:31.711 --> 36:34.496
AND IF YOU GO,
I AM GONNA MISS YOU
WAY TOO MUCH.

36:35.845 --> 36:38.283
I GOTTA GO HELP MY MOM
WITH THE RESTAURANT.

36:38.413 --> 36:40.110
YOU HAVE A GOOD SHIFT.

36:40.676 --> 36:42.243
-THANKS FOR WAKING ME UP.

36:42.374 --> 36:43.244
-ANY TIME.

36:46.639 --> 36:49.511
-AIR TRAFFIC CONTROLLER:
LEAR 4-CHARLIE-LIMA,
THIS IS LOS ANGELES TOWER.

36:49.642 --> 36:53.515
AFTER DEPARTURE, SQUAWK 1343.
CLEAR DIRECT TO
ONE-ZERO THOUSAND.

36:57.519 --> 36:59.695
-DOES THIS WORK?

36:59.826 --> 37:02.394
-WHY? YOU WANNA CALL
ONE OF YOUR FRIENDS
AND TELL THEM YOU'RE ON A PLANE?

37:02.524 --> 37:04.047
-IS IT OKAY IF I CALL MY DAD?

37:05.832 --> 37:06.920
-SURE.

37:07.050 --> 37:10.097
-HERE. THERE YOU GO.
-THANKS.

37:10.228 --> 37:13.056
-OKAY, LISTEN UP.
MATT, TOWER 12. SYDNEY, TOWER 8.

37:13.187 --> 37:15.015
CHRIS, YOU'RE AT 9.
AND, KELLY, YOU'RE AT TOWER 10.

37:15.145 --> 37:17.452
BE VERY CAREFUL OUT THERE.

37:17.583 --> 37:20.063
THE STORM LAST WEEK CREATED
SOME BIG HOLES IN THE REGULAR
BOTTOM CONTOURS.

37:20.194 --> 37:22.892
A LOT OF RIPS COMING,
ESPECIALLY ON THE SOUTH-FACING
BEACHES.

37:24.154 --> 37:25.721
THAT'S IT.

37:25.852 --> 37:27.810
-MITCH, THERE'S A PHONE CALL
FOR YOU. IT'S HOBIE.

37:27.941 --> 37:29.595
-HAVE ROD PATCH IT
TO THE TRUCK, HUH?

37:31.161 --> 37:33.163
MORNING, TINA.
-HI, MITCH.

37:35.078 --> 37:38.256
-MITCH: [ON TELEPHONE]
HOBSTER, DIDN'T EXPECT
TO HEAR FROM YOU.

37:38.386 --> 37:40.127
WHAT'S GOING ON?

37:40.258 --> 37:42.521
-DAD, GUESS WHAT.
I'M CALLING YOU
FROM KEN'S PLANE.

37:42.651 --> 37:44.827
-HEY, HOBIE, THAT'S GREAT.

37:44.958 --> 37:47.003
-SO, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

37:47.134 --> 37:49.528
-I JUST FINISHED
MORNING BRIEFING.
YOU KNOW, SAME OLD, SAME OLD.

37:49.658 --> 37:51.181
-YOU WANNA TALK TO MOM?

37:52.182 --> 37:53.793
-UH, NO THANKS, PAL.

37:53.923 --> 37:56.317
LOOK, I'M KIND OF BUSY HERE.
I GOTTA GO.

37:56.448 --> 37:59.364
-NO, DON'T HANG UP.
I WANNA TALK TO YOU
FROM THE PLANE. IT'S SO COOL.

38:00.190 --> 38:01.931
-IT'S HOBIE CALLING
FROM THE AIRPLANE.

38:05.283 --> 38:06.806
-[RUMBLING]

38:06.936 --> 38:09.156
-MITCH: [ON TELEPHONE]
HOBIE, WHAT WAS THAT NOISE?

38:09.287 --> 38:12.202
-I DON'T KNOW. IT SOUNDED LIKE
ONE OF THE ENGINES BACKFIRED
OR SOMETHING.

38:14.204 --> 38:15.293
KEN IS GONNA GO CHECK IT OUT.

38:15.423 --> 38:17.033
-[BEEPING]

38:21.299 --> 38:22.778
-WHAT IS ALL THIS VIBRATION?

38:22.909 --> 38:24.171
-ENGINE ONE IS SHUT DOWN.

38:24.302 --> 38:26.521
WE'LL HAVE TO HEAD BACK
TO THE AIRPORT.

38:26.652 --> 38:28.175
-HOW BAD IS IT?

38:28.306 --> 38:29.568
-JUST GET EVERYONE
IN THEIR SEAT BELTS, PLEASE.

38:31.221 --> 38:32.658
-HANG ON. KEN IS COMING BACK.

38:33.572 --> 38:34.573
-KEN, WHAT IS IT?

38:35.225 --> 38:36.879
-WE'VE, UH, LOST AN ENGINE.

38:37.010 --> 38:38.446
-WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

38:38.577 --> 38:40.361
-IT MEANS WE'RE GOING
BACK TO THE AIRPORT.

38:40.492 --> 38:42.407
EVERYBODY FASTEN
YOUR SEAT BELTS.

38:42.537 --> 38:44.539
WE MIGHT HAVE TO MAKE
AN EMERGENCY LANDING.

38:44.670 --> 38:46.672
-DAD, WE MAY HAVE TO MAKE
AN EMERGENCY LANDING.

38:46.802 --> 38:49.065
-HOBIE, THAT'S NOT FUNNY.

38:49.196 --> 38:51.067
-IT'S NOT A JOKE, DAD.

38:52.155 --> 38:53.722
-COME ON NOW.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

38:53.853 --> 38:55.637
HOBIE, ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

38:55.768 --> 38:58.031
-NO, DAD,
THE PLANE, EVERYTHING,
IT'S REALLY BUMPY.

39:01.556 --> 39:04.516
DAD. DAD, I'M SCARED. DAD.

39:04.646 --> 39:06.648
-ALL RIGHT, HOBIE, LISTEN TO ME.
JUST STAY CALM.

39:06.779 --> 39:08.346
-THE WHOLE PLANE IS SHAKING!

39:08.476 --> 39:09.869
-ARE YOU HEADED
BACK TO THE AIRPORT?

39:09.999 --> 39:11.174
-I DON'T KNOW.

39:11.305 --> 39:13.438
-LOOK OUT THE WINDOW.
-DAD!

39:13.568 --> 39:15.962
-WHAT DO YOU SEE, PAL?
DO YOU SEE LAND,
OR DO YOU SEE WATER?

39:18.704 --> 39:19.966
-JUST CLOUDS.

39:26.189 --> 39:27.713
-[BEEPING]
-WE'VE LOST THE OTHER ENGINE.

39:29.497 --> 39:31.369
LOSING ALTITUDE FAST.

39:32.152 --> 39:33.283
I'M DUMPING OUR FUEL.

39:35.111 --> 39:37.636
-AIR TRAFFIC CONTROLLER:
ROGER. ROGER. UNDERSTAND.
DUMPING FUEL.

39:39.942 --> 39:41.422
-[EXCLAIMS]
-WHAT? WHAT?

39:41.553 --> 39:43.163
-WE'RE GOING DOWN REALLY FAST.

39:44.294 --> 39:47.036
-AIR TRAFFIC CONTROLLER:
ROGER-LIMA, I SHOW YOU
SEVEN MILES FROM THE BEACH

39:47.167 --> 39:49.169
DESCENDING THROUGH 2,000.
WHAT ARE YOUR INTENTIONS?

39:49.299 --> 39:51.084
-GONNA TRY TO LAND ON THE WATER.

39:51.214 --> 39:53.216
-DAD, WE'RE
RIGHT OVER THE OCEAN.
WE'RE GONNA CRASH.

39:53.347 --> 39:55.741
DAD, I'M SCARED.
-HOBIE.

39:55.871 --> 39:58.570
-AIR TRAFFIC CONTROLLER:
4-CHARLIE-LIMA, BE ADVISED.
COAST GUARD HAS BEEN NOTIFIED,

39:58.700 --> 40:00.833
AND BAYWATCH RESCUE PERSONNEL
ARE ON THE WAY.

40:06.055 --> 40:07.883
4-CHARLIE-LIMA,
RESPOND IF YOU ARE ABLE.

40:15.804 --> 40:17.284
-DAD!
-HOBIE!

40:22.550 --> 40:24.247
-DAD!

40:27.555 --> 40:29.383
-[STATIC]

40:30.558 --> 40:31.472
-HOBIE?

40:32.473 --> 40:33.605
HOBIE?

40:33.735 --> 40:34.823
-MITCH, WHAT'S WRONG?

40:34.954 --> 40:36.999
-DAMN IT! PHONE WENT DEAD.

40:40.263 --> 40:41.787
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]
